GRADEVOLE broke outwards on the break, was void of early speed trailing on the fence down the backside, saved ground around the bend making little progress, passed a tiring runner turning for home on the rail but could not get into contention down the stretch. DIFFERENT DRUM pressed the issue outside down the back straight, gave way up front with challengers on each side three furlongs from the wire, backed away through the turn and had little to show in the stretch.
